7.1.5 - W11SR05: Ineffective Endpoint Application Control and Protection
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1657; Revision: 0; Updated: Dec-23; Applicability: All; OS: Windows (Implementation of Microsoft Defender for Endpoint)
•	Control: 0329; Revision: 6; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Implementation of application control)
•	Control: 1490; Revision: 1; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: Windows (Implementation of Microsoft Defender Attack Surface Reduction rules)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Insufficient or ineffective implementation of endpoint application control and protection measures including AppLocker for Stand-alone Workstations may lead to a loss of data integrity, exposure or exfiltration of sensitive information or loss of system availability.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
LIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Mandate Application Control: Deploy AppLocker or Windows Defender Application Control (WDAC) in "Enforced" mode to ensure only agency-approved and digitally signed applications can execute.
2.	Enforce Attack Surface Reduction (ASR): Enable Microsoft Defender ASR rules specifically targeting common malware vectors, such as blocking executable content from email clients and webmail.
3.	Harden Stand-alone Endpoints: Apply a rigorous security baseline to stand-alone workstations, ensuring local administrative privileges are strictly limited and all endpoint protection telemetry is logged locally.
- Treatment #1
•	AppLocker Policy Development: Generate a comprehensive whitelist based on the agency's standard operating environment (SOE) and digitally sign all bespoke internal scripts.
•	Defender for Endpoint Integration: Onboard all Windows 11 devices to Microsoft Defender for Endpoint to provide real-time detection, response, and automated investigation capabilities.
•	Audit and Review: Conduct monthly reviews of application execution logs on stand-alone workstations to identify and block unauthorised or anomalous software attempts.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
The rigorous enforcement of application control and ASR rules significantly hinders the ability of malicious code to execute or persist on the endpoint. By shifting the security posture from reactive detection to proactive whitelisting, the likelihood of a successful compromise is reduced to "Unlikely," ensuring the integrity of the stand-alone environment is maintained.
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	MEDIUM

